<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Lion's Mane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Lion's Mane (Hericium erinaceus) is a functional mushroom used for centuries in traditional Chinese and Japanese practices and one of the most studied mushrooms in modern cognitive research. Its bioactive polysaccharides, especially β-glucans, are the most measurable markers of extract quality and the focus of much of the published research."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does Lion's Mane do?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Lion's Mane is studied for its role in supporting cognitive function, memory, and long-term brain health. β-glucans and related bioactive polysaccharides are the most well-characterized actives. Most cognitive research uses daily intake over several weeks."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much Lion's Mane is in DayShift?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "DayShift contains 300 mg of a standardized Lion's Mane extract at ≥70% β-glucans, delivering the β-glucan content equivalent of approximately 2,000 mg of typical Lion's Mane extract. This is within the dose range used in clinical research on Lion's Mane and cognitive function."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between standardized and unstandardized Lion's Mane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Standardized extracts are tested to guarantee a specific percentage of active compounds. Unstandardized Lion's Mane (powders, raw mushroom, or mycelium grown on grain) can vary widely in actual bioactive content from batch to batch. β-glucans, the most measurable Lion's Mane active, are typically more concentrated in fruiting body extracts standardized to a specific β-glucan percentage. DayShift uses a USDA Organic fruiting body extract standardized to ≥70% β-glucans by Megazyme enzymatic assay."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does Lion's Mane take to work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Research on Lion's Mane and cognitive function typically measures effects after daily intake over several weeks. Effects of any supplement vary by individual and depend on overall lifestyle, sleep, nutrition, and consistency of use."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Lion's Mane safe?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Lion's Mane has been used in food and traditional practices for centuries with a strong modern safety record in clinical trials. The Lion's Mane extract used in DayShift has been notified to the FDA as GRAS (Generally Recognized as Safe), a regulatory designation few mushroom extracts hold. As with any supplement, consult your healthcare provider if you are pregnant, nursing, taking medication, or have a mushroom allergy."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

