          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">2.</span>Antioxidant activity in the fruiting body.</h4><p>The fruiting body of Lion's Mane contains antioxidant compounds studied for their role in helping the body manage everyday oxidative stress, including in neural tissue.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">3.</span>Supports the gut-brain axis.</h4><p>β-glucans act as prebiotic fiber for beneficial gut bacteria, which produce short-chain fatty acids and influence neurotransmitter activity through the gut-brain axis. The gut-brain connection is increasingly recognized as central to mood and cognitive function.</p></div>
