      <h2>Why β-Glucans Are The Metric That Matters</h2>
      <p class="bg-intro">Lion's Mane research is built on its bioactive polysaccharides. Within that family, β-glucans are the most measurable, most verifiable, and most consistently cited marker of quality. They are what researchers track when characterizing a Lion's Mane extract, and the active most often quantified in published studies.</p>

      <div class="bg-card">
        <h3>How The Math Works</h3>
        <p>A Lion's Mane supplement's β-glucan content depends on two things: how much extract is in the serving, and what percentage of that extract is actually β-glucans. Both numbers can be measured with a standardized lab method (Megazyme enzymatic assay) and reported on a Certificate of Analysis. Most Lion's Mane supplements never tell you their β-glucan content, usually because they have not measured it.</p>

        <table class="bg-math-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Source</th>
              <th>β-Glucan Content</th>
              <th>Delivered per 1,000 mg</th>
